title: The Bee-Man of Orn and Other Fanciful Tales
creator: Frank R. Stockton
description:
LibriVox recording of The Bee-Man of Orn and Other Fanciful Tales, by Frank R. Stockton. 'A collection of nine enchanting short stories filled with curious beasts and unexpected endings. Included are The Bee-Man of Orn; The Griffin and the Minor Canon; Old Pipes and the Dryad; The Queen's Museum; Christmas Before Last: Or, The Fruit of the Fragile Palm; Prince Hassak's March; The Battle of the Third Cousins; The Banished King; and The Philopena.
(summary by Gryphon Perkins) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (138MB)
subject: Librivox;audiobook;fiction;fantasy,short stories
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
this is a wonderful reading; very clear and articulate.

     if you can find it, there is also the excellent reading of Frank Stockton's "the lady or the tiger/the discourager of hesitancy"  read by Toyah with musical accompaniment by Robert Fripp ( guitarist for King Crimson) on EG records.
reviews.reviewtitle: the bee man of orn and other fanciful tales

reviews.reviewbody:
Excellent reading of these strange, medieval-sounding tales.

 Initially, I was unsure if these odd stories would hold my attention -- they did, equally due to the author's style and the reader's skill. Her voice is pure and her enunciation perfect, and has a lovely tone.  Highly recommended. 

Thank you Gryphon! More please.

TheBookworm (Manchester, UK)

At first I was a bit disconcerted by the strangeness of these tales, but they are really wonderful.  They are just the kind of highly imaginative tales one would tell to children, perhaps making them up as you go along.  The reader does a marvelous job.
